title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory Lightweight Champion Operator with extras
postcontent: This Springfield Armory Lightweight Champion Operator has been sitting idle in my safe for over three years now and hasn't been shot or carried in that time, so it's time to let it go someone who will carry, shoot, and appreciate this pistol!  Bought brand new from The Marksman in Puyallup by me, it's been carried every now and then and has less than 250 rounds of factory ammunition through it.  This pistol is unique and not like any other out there in that most of the MIM parts have been replaced with Nighthawk Custom tool steel components to include the hammer, hammer strut, and sear, as well as the mainspring housing.  The original mainspring housing also contained the ILS, which has also been removed.  An extended magazine release was added, and the trigger was cleaned up to eliminate take up and creep.  The trigger breaks very, very clean and defines the proverbial "glass rod" so often associated with crisp shooting 1911's.  The work was done by a local 1911 specialist, and all work was done by hand.  You'd have to see it to appreciate it.There's also 3M deck tape on the front strap for traction, and all grip screws have rubber washers and blue LocTite installed to avoid them backing out.  The pistol is in excellent condition save for some slight slide wear on the front contact points where it meets the holster, and a slight idiot mark on the slide from the first time I took it apart.   The night sights are also very bright and crisp, and a brand new factory recoil guide assembly is in the pistol.  The slide has never been slammed shut on an empty pistol, and extreme care has always been used when shooting and carrying this gun.  It has also been meticulously cleaned after each range session with Hoppe's Number 9 solvent, then lubed with Shooter's Choice grease where necessary and FP40 in other areas where grease was not needed.  It was also wiped down with a silicon impregnated cloth before going back into the safe.  Although it has a rail for a light, I've never installed one on it and the rail is sharp with no nicks.This pistol comes carry ready, with two stainless Wilson Combat 47D magazines, some of which are new in package and never removed, and one black Wilson Combat magazine, which blends very well with the pistol when used as the primary magazine.  A black right hand DeSantis three-slot pancake style holster and Blackhawk dual magazine pouch round out the deal. Original case and all accessories (takedown tool, two magazines, molded holster and mag pouch, barrel brush) are also included.  Asking $1050 cash - FIRM - and no trades, please.  And yes, I really do mean no trades, which means please don't ask!  Unfortunately, I do not want to be the first to get hung up with I-594, so as per Washington state law, I'm requesting a pistol transfer at either the Marksman Pistol Range in Puyallup, or the store of your choice if it's in reasonable driving distance from Pierce County.  I will pay for the transfer and cover it.  If you are unable to meet any of these requirements, then I thank you for your time.Please text me at REDACTED if you are interested.  No phone calls, please, and be ready to meet within the next day or two if you're truly interested.  Thank you for your interest!

title: For Sale:  Indoor X-Ring Centrifugal bullet trap
postcontent:
I am selling an unusual indoor bullet trap that was manufactured by X-Ring in the 1950’s or earlier.  See the attached photographs.  The trap is all steel.  The side plates were advertised as high-carbon steel.  They are welded together in the corners, which are then partially reinforced by steel angles. 
The front opening is 18” x 18”.  The sides of the trap all taper down at an 18 degree angle to a cast steel “scroll” or “snail”.  The scroll guides the bullet around in a circle until the spent bullet drops into the removable steel cup in the center of the scroll. 
The centerline height of the opening can be adjusted between 24” to 48” above the ground with an antique wrench that it included.  The trap itself can be slid up and down on the heavy steel tripod that is part of the complete unit.  The trap is reportedly good for up to 38 Special lead bullet cartridges.  I have only tried it with .22LR cartridges myself.  From what I have read, it is not suitable for Magnums, FMJ bullets, or most rifle cartridges.  Pretty much any CAS loads should be OK, though.
The trap is in good to very-good condition.  There are small amounts of surface rust here and there where the bullets have impacted.  There is no deep rust and it can be re-painted easily.
This is being sold for LOCAL PICKUP ONLY.  It is located in Omaha, NE.  The assembly weighs approx. 90 – 100 lbs.  I will help load it into the buyers pickup or SUV.  Contact Harry Owen to arrange a time to see it.  The price is $300.

title: For Sale/Trade:  WWI Berthier M16 Carbine
location: Elizabeth, Ripley, Parkersburg, Parkersburg, West Virginia
postcontent: Offered here is a French Berthier "Mousqueton de Artillerie Modèle 1892 Modifié 1916". Marked Châtellerault. This rifle is dated 1916 and is marked with the "N" on the receiver. Stock, barrel (receivers were not dated), and trigger guard match. Lock-up is tight and I have personally fired this weapon at 100 yard range and determined it is just as the little carbine is known to be --  sturdy and reliable! Fun to shoot, but kicks like a mule!Here is a link to comments on my rifle. One estimate of value was 300 Euros ($315).http://forums.gunboards.com/showthread.php?389846-New-Addition-Berthier-M-16These guns are not too often found in America. Small cut located at bottom of stock is not someone's attempt at making a sporter, but is the site of a French-done wood repair that must have fallen out over the years. This is very common. Also, slot in bottom of stock is not missing sling swivel by accident, but was removed by the French for the Artillery carbine and just never sealed up. Overall, rifle has that nice battle-damaged appearance while still offering a completely strong and serviceable rifle. A piece of history straight from WWI! Comes with 4 original 5-shot Mannlicher clips and 16 rounds of 8mm Lebel ammo (all I have leftover). Can also include 39 8mm lebel brass casings if you reload. This is a wonderful rifle, and I am only selling/ trading in the pursuit of another couple Milsurps I'm interested in. Thanks for your time and shoot me an email!P.S. Ask for more pictures!
